main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Westerville, Ohio on 29 May 1966, which was later concluded to be a meteor.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 2-3 minutes,The object was observed moving in a straight path towards the northeast,The observer reported the object having a metallic or silvery color,The report was noted by a civilian source with 5 confirmed witnesses,The study concluded the object was an astronomical event (meteor) rather than a traditional UFO.
